  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5396",
  "title": "Re-render a component in NuxtJS when SSR is used / introduce controlled mode",
  "body": "**Feature / InstantSearch V4 ⚡️**\r\n\r\n### What is your use case for such a feature?\r\n\r\nBeing able to re-render the view explicitly when a query param changes in the URL.\r\nWe see updated data coming from API but the view doesn’t re-render no matter what.\r\nWe tried with instantsearch.hydrate(this.algoliaState) without any result. \r\nIt seems that this is working only for the very first rendering of the component. ([From Carespot](https://discourse.algolia.com/t/re-render-a-component-in-nuxtjs-when-ssr-is-used/9694))\r\n\r\n### What is your proposal\r\nUpgrade vue-instantsearch to use instantsearch v4\r\nhttps://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/4362\r\n\r\n> Introducing a controlled mode in InstantSearch allows more powerful state updates coming from internal events and one-time external events.\r\n\r\n### What is the version you are using?\r\n\r\nv2.7.0\r\n\r\n",
